ACPCPE - an Amstrad CPC printer emulator DIY by Elanstra

   2019-09-01 17:30 - Genesis8

   ACPCPE is an Amstrad CPC printer emulator by Elanstra using an Arduino.
   You put it on the Amstrad CPC printer port, then connect the Arduino to
   an USB port of a PC where Python code is getting the printing job.
   Someone suggested to use a SD card to use the interface auntonomously.

   Source : CPCWiki

   Category : hardware

   twitter facebook

